KW  - Rent-seeking
KW  - Entrepreneurship
KW  - Resource booms
AB  - This paper develops a model of rent-seeking in which the opportunity cost of rent-seeking is foregone entrepreneurship. It provides conditions under which resource booms tend to lead to an increase in rent-seeking activity and those in which they induce entrepreneurship. We identify an important difference between the two activities which leads resource booms to bias gains in favour of rent-seeking over entrepreneurship. But we also show that this bias depends on the nature of the initial equilibrium.
